.SH NAME
shelly-light-set - Set light parameters


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshelly light set  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Set parameters of a light component on the specified device.

.PP
You can set brightness and on/off state.
Values not specified will be left unchanged.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-b\fP, \fB--brightness\fP=-1
	Brightness (0-100)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for set

.PP
\fB-i\fP, \fB--id\fP=0
	Light component ID (default 0)

.PP
\fB--on\fP[=false]
	Turn on


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
